      • create

        <T extends ParseObject> T create(java.lang.String className)
        Creates a Parse object of the type matching the provided class name. Defaults to the base ParseObject, i.e., call must always return a non-null object.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of ParseObject to be instantiated
        Parameters:
        className - The class name associated with type T
        Returns:
        The newly created Parse object.
